        <name>timezone_offset</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_cts_local_time::timezone_offset</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Represents the offset from UTC in number in 15-minute increments. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Valid range from -48 (<ref refid="group__bt__cts_1ga07b7421ed77c307503e154c5823ab32d" kindref="member">BT_CTS_TIMEZONE_MIN</ref>) to +56 (<ref refid="group__bt__cts_1ga204f8d7595bd169f4e547e66b8ca36b4" kindref="member">BT_CTS_TIMEZONE_MAX</ref>). A value of -128 (<ref refid="group__bt__cts_1ga38e3b4fec488ba4bcfcff097c752c32f" kindref="member">BT_CTS_TIMEZONE_DEFAULT_VALUE</ref>) means that the timezone offset is not known. All other values are Reserved for Future Use. The offset defined in this characteristic is constant regardless of whether daylight savings is in effect. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
